Differential diagnosis. The new species is very similar to
P. circularis
, from which can be separated by following characters: anterior angles of pronotum slightly projected (distinctly projected in
P. circularis
); pronotal disc always without yellow chalky material; the posterior transverse sinuate band on elytra continuous (usually divided into three parts in
P. circularis
); lateral protuberances of parameres ensiform, distinctly long and slender (protuberance auriform in
P. circularis
). This new species also resembles Vietnamese species
P. pejchai Mückstein, 2018
in appearance and parameres, but the anterior angles of pronotum is slightly projected (distinctly projected in
P. pejchai
), the color of elytra is darker, the scutellum and pronotal disc without chalky material, and the protuberances of parameres distinctly longer.
